<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="45" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,1175,2031]" pageId="8" pageNumber="45">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1175,1200]" pageId="8" pageNumber="45">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Frontal triangle pale brown, lateral margins at most gently curved, interfrontals outside frontal triangle; gena as high as postgena, about one third eye height; head broader than long in dorsal view; post–pronotum with one–two bristles; long axis of eye diagonal; scutum less than twice as long as broad with five stripes dark and pale brown; katepisternum with ventral half dark brown, with some other thin dark markings on anepisternum, mesepimeron.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
