<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,1175,2031]" pageId="8" pageNumber="45">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[201,339,1500,1524]" pageId="8" pageNumber="45">Male. Head</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[353,475,1500,1524]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 12" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1268,1291]" captionTargetBox="[200,1365,176,1241]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,145,1247]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 12. Psilochlorops, head, dorsal and lateral view. 1, 7. Psilochlorops clavitibia (holotype). 2, 8. Psilochlorops brunneus (holotype), sp. n. 3, 9. Psilochlorops nigrifemur (holotype), sp. n. 4, 10. Psilochlorops paganelliae (holotype), sp. n. 5, 11. Psilochlorops elongatum (paratype), sp. n. 6, 12. Psilochlorops flavisoma (holotype), sp. n." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/214703/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="45">Figs. 6, 12</figureCitation>
). Dark yellow, slightly wider than thorax, rather broader than long in dorsal view, longer than high in lateral view. Frontal triangle pale brown, margins at most gently curved, not reaching anterior margin of frons; occiput dark, bare; gena about 
<number box="[644,679,1572,1596]" pageId="8" pageNumber="45" value="0.2">0.2</number>
eye height; postgena about 
<number box="[994,1043,1572,1596]" pageId="8" pageNumber="45" value="0.45">0.45</number>
eye height; eye rounded, long axis diagonal; clypeus yellow with a yellowish pair of spots; labella brown; palpus yellow. First flagellomere yellow, with pale brown spot at apex; arista dark yellow. One row of interfrontals external to frontal triangle; postocellars convergent; inner and outer verticals well–developed; one row of setulae at lower margin of gena; vibrissa weak. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,240,1716,1740]" pageId="8" pageNumber="45">Thorax</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[256,350,1716,1740]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 18" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1947,1970]" captionTargetBox="[197,1394,607,1885]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,574,1926]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 18. Psilochlorops, mesonotum, dorsal view. 13. Psilochlorops clavitibia (holotype). 14. Psilochlorops brunneus (holotype), sp. n. 15. Psilochlorops nigrifemur (holotype), sp. n. 16. Psilochlorops paganelliae (holotype), sp. n. 17. Psilochlorops elongatum (paratype), sp. n. 18. Psilochlorops flavisoma (paratype), sp. n." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/214704/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="45">Figs. 18</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[362,393,1716,1740]" captionStart="FIGURES 31 – 33" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1077,1100]" captionTargetBox="[229,1382,260,1052]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[167,1427,250,1073]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 31 – 33. Psilochlorops flavisoma, sp. n. 31. Habitus (paratype). 32. Hypandrial complex, ventral view (holotype). 33. Epandrium, dorsal view (holotype). Legends, ep epandrium; hyp hypandrium; mes mesolobus; sur surstylus. Scale bar, 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/214709/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="45">31</figureCitation>
). Scutum almost twice as longer as broad, mainly yellowish, with two dark brown and three pale brown stripes, with dark pilosity; post–pronotum with a brown mark and two bristles; scutellum yellow. Pleura dark yellow, a dark brown mark dorsally on the notopleuron. Halter entirely dark yellow. Legs dark yellow; hind femur and tibia light brown; tibial organ pale yellow, elongated. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[869,933,1823,1848]" pageId="8" pageNumber="45">Wing</emphasis>
. Hyaline. Costal sections one to four: 
<date pageId="8" pageNumber="45" value="1919-07-18" valueMax="1919-07-09" valueMin="1919-07-18">
<number box="[1361,1390,1823,1847]" pageId="8" pageNumber="45" value="19.0">19</number>
- 
<number box="[1399,1428,1823,1847]" pageId="8" pageNumber="45" value="18.0">18</number>
- 
<number box="[151,167,1860,1884]" pageId="8" pageNumber="45" value="9.0">9</number>
- 
<number box="[175,191,1860,1884]" pageId="8" pageNumber="45" value="7.0">7</number>
.
</date>
R 
<number box="[220,228,1875,1889]" pageId="8" pageNumber="45" value="2.0">2</number>
+ 
<number box="[237,244,1875,1889]" pageId="8" pageNumber="45" value="3.0">3</number>
and R 
<number box="[314,322,1875,1889]" pageId="8" pageNumber="45" value="4.0">4</number>
+ 
<number box="[331,338,1875,1889]" pageId="8" pageNumber="45" value="5.0">5</number>
slightly concave; R 
<number box="[557,565,1875,1889]" pageId="8" pageNumber="45" value="4.0">4</number>
+ 
<number box="[574,581,1875,1889]" pageId="8" pageNumber="45" value="5.0">5</number>
and M 
<number box="[657,663,1875,1889]" pageId="8" pageNumber="45" value="1.0">1</number>
+ 
<number box="[673,682,1875,1889]" pageId="8" pageNumber="45" value="2.0">2</number>
rather divergent; M 
<number box="[905,911,1875,1889]" pageId="8" pageNumber="45" value="1.0">1</number>
+ 
<number box="[920,929,1875,1889]" pageId="8" pageNumber="45" value="2.0">2</number>
straight; r-m and dm-cu rather divergent, distant each other 2.0 as long as dm-cu. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[567,684,1898,1923]" pageId="8" pageNumber="45">Abdomen</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[699,782,1898,1922]" captionStart="FIGURES 31 – 33" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1077,1100]" captionTargetBox="[229,1382,260,1052]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[167,1427,250,1073]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 31 – 33. Psilochlorops flavisoma, sp. n. 31. Habitus (paratype). 32. Hypandrial complex, ventral view (holotype). 33. Epandrium, dorsal view (holotype). Legends, ep epandrium; hyp hypandrium; mes mesolobus; sur surstylus. Scale bar, 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/214709/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="45">
Fig. 
<number box="[751,782,1898,1922]" pageId="8" pageNumber="45" value="31.0">31</number>
</figureCitation>
). Tergites and sternites light brown, yellowish along distal margin. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[246,377,1934,1959]" pageId="8" pageNumber="45">Terminalia</emphasis>
. Epandrium with long ventral projections (
<figureCitation box="[874,959,1934,1958]" captionStart="FIGURES 31 – 33" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1077,1100]" captionTargetBox="[229,1382,260,1052]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[167,1427,250,1073]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 31 – 33. Psilochlorops flavisoma, sp. n. 31. Habitus (paratype). 32. Hypandrial complex, ventral view (holotype). 33. Epandrium, dorsal view (holotype). Legends, ep epandrium; hyp hypandrium; mes mesolobus; sur surstylus. Scale bar, 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/214709/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="45">
Fig. 
<number box="[928,959,1934,1958]" pageId="8" pageNumber="45" value="33.0">33</number>
</figureCitation>
); mesolobus reduced, weakly sclerotized; surstylus short partially fused to epandrium; hypandrium with fine apical extensions (
<figureCitation box="[1108,1193,1970,1994]" captionStart="FIGURES 31 – 33" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1077,1100]" captionTargetBox="[229,1382,260,1052]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[167,1427,250,1073]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 31 – 33. Psilochlorops flavisoma, sp. n. 31. Habitus (paratype). 32. Hypandrial complex, ventral view (holotype). 33. Epandrium, dorsal view (holotype). Legends, ep epandrium; hyp hypandrium; mes mesolobus; sur surstylus. Scale bar, 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/214709/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="45">
Fig. 
<number box="[1161,1193,1970,1994]" pageId="8" pageNumber="45" value="32.0">32</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,1175,2031]" box="[201,402,2007,2031]" pageId="8" pageNumber="45">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[201,295,2007,2031]" pageId="8" pageNumber="45">Female.</emphasis>
